ul
  li DO use a &lt;html lang="de" &gt; tag representing the current page language
  li DO use a meaningful page title. See diveintoaccessibility
  li DO provide link tags for navigation support. (e.g. &lt;link rel="home" href="https://axa.ch" /&gt;) See diveintoaccessibility
  li DO use meaningful alt texts on ALL img elements
  li DO use the acronym element to explain the first usage of an acronym and mark this visualy
  li DO provide a summary for tables
  li DO use real h1 through h6 tags for your headings
  li DO make everything searchable. Every page needs a search field, preferably above the formfield
  li DO use common accesskey's (e.g. 0: accessiblity statement, 1: home, ...)
  li DO use landmarks to categorize content
    ul
      li DO use the role="main" landmark for your main content area
      li DO use the role="complementary" landmark for complementary information
      li DO use the role="search" landmark for your page search
      li DO use the role="navigation" landmark for all areas used to navigate (e.g. main navigation, tabs, ...)
      li DO use the role="banner" landmark to mark content that is site and not page specific
      li See <a href="https://www.paciellogroup.com/blog/2013/02/using-wai-aria-landmarks-2013/" >https://www.paciellogroup.com/blog/2013/02/using-wai-aria-landmarks-2013/</a>for further landmarks
      li DO NOT have any content that is not assigned to a landmark
      li DO use the HTML5 elements (nav, main, header) in conjunction with the role attribute, but DO NOT rely on them alone. See the link above for the matching of HTML5 to landmarks
  li DO make your website/app navigable with the keyboard. This not only improves accessiblity but also allows power user to use your app more efficently. See <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/Keyboard-navigable_JavaScript_widgets" >https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/Keyboard-navigable_JavaScript_widgets</a>
    ul
      li DO use tabindex to mark elements as tab navigable or remove the ability to tab into it
      li Be careful when using nested tabindex. This would require manual focus handling. See the link above for further information.
      li See the best practices mention in the article above.
